HEADWORD: Goosewing
<hw>Goose"wing`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>One of the clews or lower corners of a course or a topsail when the
middle part or the rest of the sail is furled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goosewinged</ent>⟦br⟧
